
1. Copy the files to your own directory.

2. Modify inet.h to reflect the host you are currently logged into.
   Also, modify the port numbers to be used to reduce the likelihood
   of conflicting with another server.

3. Compile the source code using the command: make

4. Start the directory server in the background or in its own terminal: ./directoryServer5 [&]

5. Start one or more chat servers in the background or in their own terminal: ./chatServer5 <"Chat Topic"> <Port Number> [&]
   The only valid topics are "Anime", "Sports", or "Video Games".
   Any other topic will use the certificate and key for Anime, and will fail verification when a client tries to connect.
	
5. Start the client on the same or another host in the foreground: ./chatClient5

6. Select an index of a chat server to join it.

7. Remember to kill the server before logging off.
